            <TextArea editable="false" maxHeight="400.0" maxWidth="500.0" prefHeight="230.0" prefWidth="460.0" text="Planting Crops: &#10;- Click the &quot;Select Crop&quot; button at the bottom of the screen. &#10;- A drop-down menu will appear -- choose the crop you want to plant. &#10;- Once selected, click any &quot;Plant&quot; button in the middle of the screen to plant it. &#10;&#10;Growth Times:&#10;- Different crops take different number of days to grow.&#10;- The growth time is shown on each plot.&#10;- You cannot plant a new crop on a plot until the current one is finished. &#10;- To advance the game, click the &quot;Next Day&quot; button. &#10;&#10;TIP: Use Help -&gt; Crop Info to view the stats of all crops. &#10;&#10;Harvesting Crops: &#10;- When a crop is ready, it can be harvested and fed to a villager. &#10;- There are two ways to feed a villager:&#10;&#10;1. &quot;Select Villager&quot; button&#10;- Click the &quot;Select Villager&quot; button&#10;- Choose which villager to feed from the drop-down menu.&#10;- Then click on the ready crop to feed it.&#10;&#10;2. Drag and Drop&#10;- Click and hold on a ready crop.&#10;- Drag it onto a villager's image.&#10;- Release the mouse, and the villager will eat the crop.&#10;&#10;Villagers: &#10;- Each villager starts with nutrition level of 50.&#10;- Nutrition level decreases each day if they are not fed. &#10;- If they eat the same type of crop too many times in a row, their nutrition level will also drop. &#10;- Keep them alive by feeding them regularly with a variety of crops. &#10;&#10;Winning/Losing: &#10;- You win if: &#10;     - All villagers are alive, and &#10;     - All villagers reach full nutrition level (100)&#10;- You lose if: &#10;     - All villagers die of hunger or malnutrition.&#10;" wrapText="true" GridPane.columnSpan="3" GridPane.rowIndex="1" />
